This paper focuses on sentiment analysis of product reviews, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of supervised sequence labeling, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the idea of concept sharing across multiple domains, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
